## [1.3.1-alpha] - 2026-03-01

### WAV Audio Streaming for Chromecast (Sprint 21b)

#### Added
- **WAV audio streaming endpoint** (`GET /audio`): HTTP endpoint serving
  infinite WAV stream (mono PCM 16-bit, 44100 Hz) from PSG audio output.
  Enables Chromecast to play ORIC-1 sound via `<audio>` HTML element.
- **Audio ring buffer** in `cast_server_t`: 2-second circular buffer
  (`CAST_AUDIO_RING_SAMPLES = 88200`) with mutex-protected write access
  and per-client read positions (up to 4 audio clients).
- **Stereo-to-mono downmix**: `cast_server_push_audio()` receives stereo
  PCM from SDL2 audio callback and writes mono average to ring buffer.
- **WAV header builder** `cast_build_wav_header()`: generates 44-byte
  RIFF/WAV header with infinite data size (`0x7FFFFFFF`) for streaming.
- **Audio forwarding hook**: `audio_set_cast_server()` connects SDL2
  audio callback to cast server. Called from `audio_callback()` after
  `ay_generate()` to stream PSG audio in real-time.
- **HTML `<audio autoplay>`**: cast viewer page at `/` now includes
  `<audio autoplay><source src="/audio" type="audio/wav">` for automatic
  sound playback on Chromecast.
- **3 new audio streaming unit tests**: WAV header validity (44 bytes,
  RIFF/WAVE/fmt/data, PCM mono 44100 16-bit), ring buffer push (stereo
  downmix verification), ring buffer wrap-around (circular write).
- **Web Audio API low-latency playback**: HTML page uses `fetch()` with
  `ReadableStream` reader + `AudioContext` to decode PCM chunks and
  schedule playback with ~100ms buffer. Replaces `<audio>` element
  which had 2-5s browser buffering. Drift correction resets schedule
  if >500ms ahead. Autoplay with click fallback for Chrome policy.

#### Changed
- `cast_server.h`: added `CAST_AUDIO_*` constants, audio ring buffer
  fields, `audio_mutex`, `audio_clients[]`/`audio_read_pos[]` arrays,
  `cast_server_push_audio()` and `cast_build_wav_header()` declarations,
  stub for non-CAST builds.
- `cast_server.c`: `/audio` route with WAV header + streaming, audio
  client management, `broadcast_audio()` in server loop, audio mutex
  init/destroy in lifecycle.
- `audio_output.c`: `audio_set_cast_server()` implementation, cast
  server push call in SDL2 `audio_callback()`.
- `audio.h`: `audio_set_cast_server()` declaration.
- `main.c`: wiring `audio_set_cast_server()` after cast server init.
- Version updated from 1.3.0-alpha to 1.3.1-alpha.
